{"lemma":"ثُمامِ","slug":"ثُمامِ","root":"ث.م.م","root_slug":"ث-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4669"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8F%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"panicgrass (Panicum)","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ث م م (ṯ m m) which means in the base stem “to repair, to put in a good state”, for this plant has been used for thatching huts, bags have been covered with it to protect contents from the sun, and other mendings are undertaken with it."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4669","headword_ar":"ثُمَامٌ","root":"vm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Panicum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"panic grass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to several species thereof; but restricted by Forskål (Flor. Aeg. Ar., descr. plant., p. 20, where its Arabic name is written “ tummâm, ” ) to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"panicum dichotomum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"called by Delile (Flor. Aeg., no. 58, where its Arabic name is written “ temâm, ” )"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pennisetum dichotomum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and described by him in the “ explication des planches ” accompanying his Flora, plate 8:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Arabs use it for making thatch for their huts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Msb, K, [in the M termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarN","text_ar":"شَجَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known in the desert, not desired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not much eaten, by the camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cattle, except in a case of scarcity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drought;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frail; having what are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuwS","text_ar":"خُوص"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or what resemble"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xwS","text_ar":"خوص"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes used for stuffing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and for stopping up the interstices of houses;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sometimes used for removing whiteness from the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is of several species, one of which is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEap","text_ar":"ضَعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and another is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaliylap","text_ar":"جَلِيلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and another is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaf","text_ar":"غَرَف"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which resembles rushes"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usal","text_ar":"اُسَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and brooms are made of it, and water-bags are covered with it to protect them from the sun, causing the water to become cool:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umoSuwxapN","text_ar":"اُمْصُوخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] it is also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vayomuwmN","text_ar":"ثَيْمُومٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓, [but see what follows,] (T, M,) which is sometimes contracted into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vumapN","text_ar":"ثُمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T;) or it is also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~N","text_ar":"ثُمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~apN","text_ar":"ثُمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un.: (AHn, TA:) the n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vumaAmN","text_ar":"ثُمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [likewise] with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, Msb, K.) You say of a thing that may be reached, or taken with the hand, without difficulty, (T, Z, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa EalaY Tarafi Alv~umaAmi","text_ar":"هُوَ عَلَى طَرَفِ الثُّمَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, T, M, Z, K, *,) i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is easy to thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"within thy reach, no obstacle intervening between thee and it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M:) because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vmAm","text_ar":"ثمام"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not tall, (T, K,) so that the reaching it should be difficult. (T.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa laka EalaY raA^osi Alv~um~api","text_ar":"هُوَ لَكَ عَلَى رَاْسِ الثُّمَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the same]. (M.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa EalaY raA^osi Alv~um~api","text_ar":"هُوَ عَلَى رَاْسِ الثُّمَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka *`lika","text_ar":"لَكَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY raA^osi Alv~um~api","text_ar":"عَلَى رَاْسِ الثُّمَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is easy of attainment to thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M,) is a prov. used in relation to the attainment of a thing that one wants. (M, TA.) The Arabs also say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^abuwhu EalaY Tarafi Alv~um~api","text_ar":"هُوَ اَبُوهُ عَلَى طَرَفِ الثُّمَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is like his father:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and some of them say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~am~ap","text_ar":"الثَّمَّة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h. (TA.) And it is said in a trad. of 'Omar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AugozuwA waAlgazowu HulowN xaDirN","text_ar":"اُغْزُوا وَالغَزْوُ حُلْوٌ خَضِرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabola A^ano yaSiyra vumaAmFA vum~a rumaAmFA vum~a HuTaAmFA","text_ar":"قَبْلَ اَنْ يَصِيرَ ثُمَامًا ثُمَّ رُمَامًا ثُمَّ حُطَامًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Engage ye in predatory warfare while it is sweet and fresh"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning, while ye see, and make abundant, your spoils,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before it become feeble like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vmAm","text_ar":"ثمام"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"page_break","n":352},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"then, decayed; then, broken up."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA.) ―         -b2-  It also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What has become dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dried up, of the branches that are placed beneath the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDad","text_ar":"نَضَد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K","T","M","AHn","Z","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}